data.title: Good Chicago style hot dogs
data.text: I love my Chicago hot dogs and Dayne's does a credible job. Good snap to the dog with appropriate accompaniments. Good fries. Worth a trip for a dawg lover.

data.title: There's no better sandwich in town
data.text: Chicago food--done right!  Italian beef is as good as any joint in Chicago.  Perfect Chicago dog.  The deep dish pizza is the only "real" in all of LA.  Have a beef with sweet and hot wet and live!!

data.title: Excellent food, great staff-A taste of the midwest
data.text: Haven't tried many of the items on the menu as I tend to focus on the beef sandwiches.  However, the deep dish pizza was excellent and quite filling (It lasted a few meals.).  Everything we've had is worth returning for.  Oh, and Dayne is a treasure!

data.title: Good dog
data.text: One of my kids wanted a hot dog for lunch.  I guess Wienerschnitzal closed so we gave this place a try.  The chili cheese dog was good.  We will be back.

data.title: Tough
data.text: The skin on the Chicago Dogs is too tough. I spent the first 22 years of my life in Chicago and the dogs were great - skins were not tough. All the peppers you could eat were included.

data.title: Big Da Beef not bad but expensive and not an Italian Beef
data.text: Not an Italian Beef - people from Greater Chicagoland will nod their heads knowing what I'm talking about then shake their heads in disbelief that yet another imposter has dared to call themselves an Italian Beef.  A proper Italian Beef has peppers, additional spices, and has so much au jus it needs to be eaten with a knife and fork.  This is a French Dip although its not served with an au jus cup.  The bun is toasted and heavily dipped.  Its a good version, good au jus, good quality beef, decent bun, but not an Italian Beef and a kinda costly at $10.50 especially for the amount.

data.title: Great for a quick lunch
data.text: I've stopped in several times the past few months and their Vienna beef hot dogs (lots of combination choices) have been consistently good. I tried the meatball sandwich on my last visit and it was great. Good parking and friendly, quick service. I will definitely return.

data.title: Tasty!
data.text: Good place to go if you like Custom style Hot Dogs, They have a lot to try and plenty of outdoor seating. Give it a try!

data.title: Good lunch spot
data.text: This is a good lunch spot in a town seriously lacking little neighborhood joints. Not the best Chicago dog you'll ever have but for Thousand Oaks Dayne's is a welcome addition. The dogs are not too crispy but come with interesting choices of toppings.  I recommend the sweet potato tots with ranch . Delish .

data.title: Little Gem
data.text: Newer little place in Thousand Oaks - had a Vienna Beef hot dog with mustard and relish, and the relish was homemade I think because it was the VERY BEST I have ever tasted!  Another time my family and I went and got the deep dish pan pizza, takes about 40 minutes to cook so order ahead, it was very small for the price but very good.  Not really a pizza that is sized to share with more than 2 people, they told us it was plenty for all 3 of us but it was not.  Was more of the size of a personal pan pizza and maybe a slice larger.  Anyways, food is great and service is very good, very attentive staff.  Eating area inside is very small - but if weather is nice they have a large outdoor patio with seating.  Enjoy!

data.title: Great Hot Dogs
data.text: I have mixed feelings about Dayne's.  On the one hand, the Chicago Dog was really good.  But the rest of the options were ordinary.  For example the fries were hardly as original and really not exceptional.  It's nice that you can sit outside.  But one good reason to lunch at Dayne's, is that you can go next door after lunch to Chocolatine for dessert!

data.title: Tasty Dogs
data.text: Chicago style hot dogs were good.  looking forward to trying the other dogs and sandwiches they offer.  Great staff, very friendly and helpful with suggestions.
